{
  "stem": "2539.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I-- I remember one thing, that we had a caretaker in the building and his daughter went crazy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember she was locked up in a cellar which had doors, open doors.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were only like in a zoo, the crates, metal crates.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this girl cried and screamed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She obviously must-- now looking back, she must've been a schizophrenic.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was a terrific, terribly traumatic experience to me to see that they lock up a human being who's in pain and allow this girl, summer or winter-- no, I think it took maybe six months for her, a matter of months for her being there and they removed her, obviously, somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But this left such a mark on me, how unfair of the parents to lock up a young girl who is in pain and listen to her scream and do nothing about it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I coped with it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was painful but-- it was painful, of course, but I had no choice.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And don't forget that I went already to the kindergarten, probably.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I only had it weekends, maybe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in any case, I remember this as a very traumatic experience.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father used to come and visit us very often.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then eventually, of course, we packed our household and we went and joined him in Lutsk and he bought a house there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Originally, we lived in a house by the mill.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were three other families living there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a very big house and we had a quarter of the house with a separate entrance, of course.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then very soon after, my father bought a beautiful house with-- there was-- there were people living there with three sons and they had an enormous tennis court.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
